    <briefdescription>
<para>Same as Champs_compris, but specialised for IJK fields and also supports quering for vectorial fields (aka IJK_Field_vector3_double). </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Note that this class has no member of type &quot;Champs_compris_IJK&quot;. This member is kept separate and inserted in <ref refid="classNavier__Stokes__FTD__IJK" kindref="compound">Navier_Stokes_FTD_IJK</ref>, <ref refid="classIJK__Interfaces" kindref="compound">IJK_Interfaces</ref>, etc., because in some cases (typically at the probleme level <ref refid="classProbleme__FTD__IJK__base" kindref="compound">Probleme_FTD_IJK_base</ref>) we do not need the member, just the abstract interface below. </para>
